President Obama signed the Korean War Veterans Recognition Act on July 28, 2009, which adds National Korean War Veterans Armistice Day to the list of days where the display of the US flag is encouraged. The bill was sponsored by Rep. Charles Rangel and passed unanimously in both the House of Representatives and the Senate. President Obama proclaimed July 27, 2009, as National Korean War Veterans Armistice Day. The President expressed gratitude and respect for the veterans of the Korean War and acknowledged their sacrifices in pursuit of freedom and democracy for the Korean peninsula.